snippet.textDisplay:
REPLY TO MR JUNAID SAIF
Really it is a shame , how our artist are treated back home. I did not know him , left pakistan in 2000, glad I did , Zohaib and Nazia were our neighbours and our parents friends, just saw them at Karachi Gymkhana and said hello.
Mr Zaki now when I see his music and talent , it went to waste so early, may he rest in peace. He looked so calm and had a very nice personility. I also wish something must have been done.Edhi sahab has done wonders in Pakistan, if we do a little it does become a big deal altogether , so how come never someone did something for Mr zaki.
God blessPakistan and all the human race there, as it is getting worse day by day , human life is not valued there.
There should be a relief fund for artsts there, I saw Roohi Bano the great actress interview , how she lives and what is she going through, hope God give this country courage so they can rise to the great future. Ameen
Sabina Canada
